## M19(4/6): unsafe fn calling another unsafe fn directly is OK.
##
## Per the Rust-style "unsafe fn body is unsafe context" rule
## (GPT-5.5 entry 35): the entire body of an unsafe fn is an
## unsafe context, so calls to other unsafe fns don't need an
## explicit `unsafe` block.

unsafe sub low_level()
  print(1)

unsafe sub high_level()
  low_level()      # OK: body of unsafe fn is unsafe context

sub main()
  unsafe
    high_level()
